# Tailwind CSS v4 Standards

## Rules

- Use Tailwind utility classes instead of custom CSS.
- Use design tokens from `tailwind.config.ts` for colors and spacing.
- Follow mobile-first responsive design with breakpoints.
- Use consistent spacing scale: `p-4`, `p-6`, `gap-4`, `gap-6`.
- Use semantic color tokens: `primary`, `debt`, `credit`, `neutral`.
- Avoid magic numbers: use Tailwind classes instead of arbitrary values.
- Use consistent border radius: `rounded-xl` or `rounded-2xl` for cards.
- Use consistent typography classes from design system.

## Design Tokens

- Use `primary` color for primary actions (violet-600: `#7C3AED`).
- Use `debt` color for negative amounts (red-500: `#EF4444`).
- Use `credit` color for positive amounts (emerald-500: `#10B981`).
- Use `neutral` color for secondary text (slate-500: `#64748B`).
- Use `background` for page backgrounds (slate-50: `#F8FAFC`).
- Use `surface` for card backgrounds (white: `#FFFFFF`).

## Typography

- Use `font-heading` for headings (Plus Jakarta Sans).
- Use `font-body` for body text (Inter).
- Use consistent font weights: `font-semibold` (600), `font-bold` (700).
- Use consistent text sizes: `text-sm`, `text-base`, `text-lg`, `text-xl`, `text-2xl`, `text-3xl`.

## Spacing

- Use consistent spacing scale: `p-4`, `p-6`, `p-8` for padding.
- Use `gap-4`, `gap-6` for flex/grid gaps.
- Use `space-y-4`, `space-y-6` for vertical spacing.
- Use `mb-4`, `mb-6`, `mt-4`, `mt-6` for margins.
- Avoid arbitrary spacing values like `p-[13px]`.

## Colors

- Use semantic color tokens from config: `bg-primary`, `text-primary`.
- Use Tailwind color scale: `bg-violet-600`, `text-slate-900`, `bg-slate-50`.
- Use opacity modifiers: `bg-primary/10`, `text-slate-500/80`.
- Use hover states: `hover:bg-violet-700`, `hover:text-violet-600`.

## Border Radius

- Use `rounded-xl` (12px) for cards and containers.
- Use `rounded-2xl` (16px) for modals and prominent cards.
- Use `rounded-lg` (8px) for buttons and inputs.
- Use `rounded-full` for pills and avatars.

## Shadows

- Use `shadow-lg` for cards and elevated surfaces.
- Use `shadow-md` for subtle elevation.
- Use `shadow-sm` for minimal depth.
- Avoid custom shadow values unless necessary.

## Responsive Design

- Use mobile-first approach: base styles for mobile, then `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`.
- Use breakpoints: `sm:` (640px), `md:` (768px), `lg:` (1024px).
- Design primarily for mobile (360px - 430px width).
- Use responsive utilities: `px-4 md:px-8`, `text-base md:text-lg`.

